Alice: Haha. Yes, me too. I really enjoy playing, but I never gamble. :)

Bob: Oh... I don't gamble on Big2 either, except for one time a few weeks ago.

Alice: Was that with Joe a few weeks ago?

Bob: I went to a friend's house. He wanted to play Big2, so I said sure. Then he said, "Let's bet one cent per card" (because he plays very well). I almost said, "No way!" But I thought, "At most, I'll only lose about $10," so I played.

Alice: Oh, I see. :) Hehe. You're right, it's actually okay. But if you're not willing to gamble, I wouldn't enjoy the game as much.

Bob: But it's not good to be too stubborn, right? Yeah, if you have to gamble, it gets very stressful. By the way, do you have the game program?

Alice: The program? No, I don't. Did you download it or something? :)

Bob: Of course, to play online you need the program. My chat client can't send files yet. Maybe you can get it from me via FTP or HTTP... wait...

Alice: Oh, okay. :) No need to worry. Hehe. [end of text]


